---
// CalculatorSEOInfo.astro
---
<section class="py-24 border-b border-b1 bg-bg relative overflow-hidden" id="calculator-guide">
  <!-- Background decorative elements -->
  <div class="absolute top-0 left-1/2 -translate-x-1/2 w-[800px] h-[400px] bg-accent/5 rounded-full blur-[100px] pointer-events-none"></div>

  <div class="max-w-[1200px] mx-auto px-5 md:px-10 relative z-10">
    <div class="text-center max-w-3xl mx-auto mb-16">
      <span class="inline-block text-[11px] font-bold tracking-[0.1em] uppercase text-accent mb-2.5">Comprehensive Guide</span>
      <h2 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-semibold tracking-tight text-t1 leading-[1.15] mb-4">Mastering Your Overtime Pay</h2>
      <p class="text-[15px] md:text-base text-t2 leading-[1.7]">
        Understanding how your overtime is calculated can help you ensure you are fairly compensated. 
        Learn the ins and outs of pay periods, multipliers, and labor laws to maximize your earnings.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-3 gap-6 md:gap-8 mb-16">
      <!-- Card 1 -->
      <div class="bg-s2 border border-b1 rounded-2xl p-8 hover:border-accent/40 transition-colors duration-300 group">
        <div class="w-12 h-12 bg-bg border border-b1 rounded-xl flex items-center justify-center mb-6 group-hover:-translate-y-1 transition-transform duration-300">
          <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke-width="1.5" stroke="currentColor" class="w-6 h-6 text-accent">
            <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M12 6v6h4.5m4.5 0a9 9 0 11-18 0 9 9 0 0118 0z" />
          </svg>
        </div>
        <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-t1 mb-3">Time and a Half (1.5x)</h3>
        <p class="text-sm text-t2 leading-relaxed mb-4">
          The standard federal requirement under the Fair Labor Standards Act (FLSA). You must receive at least 1.5 times your regular hourly rate for any hours worked over 40 in a workweek.
        </p>
        <ul class="text-sm text-t2 flex flex-col gap-2">
          <li class="flex items-center gap-2">
            <svg class="w-4 h-4 text-green" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M5 13l4 4L19 7"></path></svg>
            Standard for most US workers
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-center gap-2">
            <svg class="w-4 h-4 text-green" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M5 13l4 4L19 7"></path></svg>
            Applies after 40 hours/week
          </li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <!-- Card 2 -->
      <div class="bg-s2 border border-b1 rounded-2xl p-8 hover:border-accent/40 transition-colors duration-300 group">
        <div class="w-12 h-12 bg-bg border border-b1 rounded-xl flex items-center justify-center mb-6 group-hover:-translate-y-1 transition-transform duration-300">
          <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke-width="1.5" stroke="currentColor" class="w-6 h-6 text-green">
            <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M12 6v12m-3-2.818l.879.659c1.171.879 3.07.879 4.242 0 1.172-.879 1.172-2.303 0-3.182C13.536 12.219 12.768 12 12 12c-.725 0-1.45-.22-2.003-.659-1.106-.879-1.106-2.303 0-3.182s2.9-.879 4.006 0l.415.33M21 12a9 9 0 11-18 0 9 9 0 0118 0z" />
          </svg>
        </div>
        <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-t1 mb-3">Double Time (2.0x)</h3>
        <p class="text-sm text-t2 leading-relaxed mb-4">
          Not federally mandated, but required in certain states like California. Usually applies when working over 12 hours in a single day, or working on the 7th consecutive day.
        </p>
        <ul class="text-sm text-t2 flex flex-col gap-2">
          <li class="flex items-center gap-2">
            <svg class="w-4 h-4 text-green" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M5 13l4 4L19 7"></path></svg>
            State-specific requirements
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-center gap-2">
            <svg class="w-4 h-4 text-green" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M5 13l4 4L19 7"></path></svg>
            Applies to extreme hours
          </li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <!-- Card 3 -->
      <div class="bg-s2 border border-b1 rounded-2xl p-8 hover:border-accent/40 transition-colors duration-300 group">
        <div class="w-12 h-12 bg-bg border border-b1 rounded-xl flex items-center justify-center mb-6 group-hover:-translate-y-1 transition-transform duration-300">
          <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke-width="1.5" stroke="currentColor" class="w-6 h-6 text-t1">
            <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M6.75 3v2.25M17.25 3v2.25M3 18.75V7.5a2.25 2.25 0 012.25-2.25h13.5A2.25 2.25 0 0121 7.5v11.25m-18 0A2.25 2.25 0 005.25 21h13.5A2.25 2.25 0 0021 18.75m-18 0v-7.5A2.25 2.25 0 015.25 9h13.5A2.25 2.25 0 0121 11.25v7.5m-9-6h.008v.008H12v-.008zM12 15h.008v.008H12V15zm0 2.25h.008v.008H12v-.008zM9.75 15h.008v.008H9.75V15zm0 2.25h.008v.008H9.75v-.008zM7.5 15h.008v.008H7.5V15zm0 2.25h.008v.008H7.5v-.008zm6.75-4.5h.008v.008h-.008v-.008zm0 2.25h.008v.008h-.008V15zm0 2.25h.008v.008h-.008v-.008zm2.25-4.5h.008v.008H16.5v-.008zm0 2.25h.008v.008H16.5V15z" />
          </svg>
        </div>
        <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-t1 mb-3">Pay Periods Explained</h3>
        <p class="text-sm text-t2 leading-relaxed mb-4">
          Your take-home pay depends on your pay frequency. Our detailed calculator automatically scales your hourly wages into bi-weekly, monthly, and yearly estimates.
        </p>
        <ul class="text-sm text-t2 flex flex-col gap-2">
          <li class="flex items-center gap-2">
            <svg class="w-4 h-4 text-green" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M5 13l4 4L19 7"></path></svg>
            Bi-weekly (26 checks/yr)
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-center gap-2">
            <svg class="w-4 h-4 text-green" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M5 13l4 4L19 7"></path></svg>
            Semi-monthly (24 checks/yr)
          </li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- SEO Rich Text Area -->
    <div class="bg-bg border border-b1 rounded-3xl p-8 md:p-12 shadow-sm mb-12">
      <div class="prose prose-invert max-w-none">
        <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-t1 mb-6 tracking-tight">How to Use the Advanced Overtime Calculator</h3>
        
        <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-10">
          <div>
            <p class="text-t2 text-[15px] leading-relaxed mb-5">
              Calculating exact wages can be tedious when juggling base rates, overtime hours, and different pay frequencies. This <strong>advanced overtime pay calculator</strong> removes the guesswork. Simply input your base pay rate (whether it's hourly, daily, weekly, or yearly) and your expected overtime hours.
            </p>
            <p class="text-t2 text-[15px] leading-relaxed mb-5">
              The tool instantly computes your regular pay, overtime pay, and generates a complete paycheck breakdown. This is highly useful for freelancers, hourly workers, and salaried employees checking their converted hourly rates.
            </p>
          </div>
          
          <div class="bg-s2 border border-b1 rounded-2xl p-6">
            <h4 class="text-lg font-semibold text-t1 mb-4">Why Calculate Overtime Accurately?</h4>
            <ul class="space-y-3">
              <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
                <div class="mt-0.5 flex-shrink-0 w-5 h-5 rounded-full bg-accent/20 flex items-center justify-center">
                  <span class="w-1.5 h-1.5 rounded-full bg-accent"></span>
                </div>
                <span class="text-sm text-t2 leading-snug"><strong>Budgeting & Planning:</strong> Accurately forecast your monthly and yearly take-home pay based on fluctuating overtime hours.</span>
              </li>
              <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
                <div class="mt-0.5 flex-shrink-0 w-5 h-5 rounded-full bg-green/20 flex items-center justify-center">
                  <span class="w-1.5 h-1.5 rounded-full bg-green"></span>
                </div>
                <span class="text-sm text-t2 leading-snug"><strong>Wage Verification:</strong> Ensure your employer is correctly applying the 1.5x or 2.0x multipliers to your gross pay.</span>
              </li>
              <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
                <div class="mt-0.5 flex-shrink-0 w-5 h-5 rounded-full bg-t1/10 flex items-center justify-center">
                  <span class="w-1.5 h-1.5 rounded-full bg-t2"></span>
                </div>
                <span class="text-sm text-t2 leading-snug"><strong>Job Comparisons:</strong> Compare job offers with different base salaries but varying expected overtime hours.</span>
              </li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- More Simple English Information -->
    <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-8">
      <div class="bg-bg border border-b1 rounded-3xl p-8 shadow-sm hover:border-accent/30 transition-colors">
        <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-t1 mb-4 flex items-center gap-3">
          <div class="w-10 h-10 rounded-full bg-accent/10 flex items-center justify-center text-accent">
            <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke-width="2" stroke="currentColor" class="w-5 h-5">
              <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M12 6v6h4.5m4.5 0a9 9 0 11-18 0 9 9 0 0118 0z" />
            </svg>
          </div>
          The 40-Hour Rule Simply Explained
        </h3>
        <p class="text-t2 text-[15px] leading-relaxed mb-4">
          In the United States, a standard workweek is 40 hours. If you work <strong>more than 40 hours</strong> in a single week, those extra hours count as overtime.
        </p>
        <p class="text-t2 text-[15px] leading-relaxed mb-4">
          For example: If you work 45 hours this week, you get paid your normal rate for the first 40 hours. The extra 5 hours are paid at your overtime rate (which is usually time-and-a-half).
        </p>
        <div class="bg-s2 rounded-xl p-4 border border-b1">
          <p class="text-sm text-t1 font-medium"><span class="text-green font-bold">Quick tip:</span> Your overtime is calculated by the week, not by the day! Even if you work 10 hours on Monday, you won't get overtime unless your total hours for the week go over 40 (except in states like California that have daily limits).</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-bg border border-b1 rounded-3xl p-8 shadow-sm hover:border-green/30 transition-colors">
        <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-t1 mb-4 flex items-center gap-3">
          <div class="w-10 h-10 rounded-full bg-green/10 flex items-center justify-center text-green">
            <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke-width="2" stroke="currentColor" class="w-5 h-5">
              <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M15.75 6a3.75 3.75 0 11-7.5 0 3.75 3.75 0 017.5 0zM4.501 20.118a7.5 7.5 0 0114.998 0A17.933 17.933 0 0112 21.75c-2.676 0-5.216-.584-7.499-1.632z" />
            </svg>
          </div>
          Hourly vs. Salaried: Who Gets It?
        </h3>
        <p class="text-t2 text-[15px] leading-relaxed mb-4">
          Not everyone is eligible for overtime pay. The rules usually depend on how you are paid and what kind of work you do.
        </p>
        <ul class="space-y-4 mb-4">
          <li class="flex items-start gap-3 text-[15px] text-t2">
            <svg class="w-5 h-5 text-green shrink-0 mt-0.5" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M5 13l4 4L19 7"></path></svg>
            <div><strong class="text-t1 block mb-0.5">Hourly Workers:</strong> Yes! Almost all hourly workers must be paid overtime when they work more than 40 hours.</div>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-3 text-[15px] text-t2">
            <svg class="w-5 h-5 text-accent shrink-0 mt-0.5" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M12 9v2m0 4h.01m-6.938 4h13.856c1.54 0 2.502-1.667 1.732-3L13.732 4c-.77-1.333-2.694-1.333-3.464 0L3.34 16c-.77 1.333.192 3 1.732 3z"></path></svg>
            <div><strong class="text-t1 block mb-0.5">Salaried Workers:</strong> It depends. If you make less than $43,888 a year (as of 2024), you usually qualify. If you make more, you might be "exempt" and not get overtime.</div>
          </li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
